{In this very instructive blitz game of mine, my opponent allowed f5-f4 and
was simply...destroyed! Study the analysis of the possible alternatives!} 1. d4
Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 c5 5. Nf3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 d6 7. Bd3 ({Entering an
endgame would be a big mistake:} 7. dxc5 $2 dxc5 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 {White only has
a temporary initiative with for example} 9. Ba3 b6 10. Ne5 Ke7 11. Be2 Bb7 {
Black has defended against everything and can now exploit White's pawn
weaknesses. Black can attack c4 with superior forces. For example} 12. O-O Nfd7
13. Nxd7 Kxd7 $17 {[%csl Rc4][%cal Yb8c6,Yc6a5,Yb7a6,Ya6c4,Ya5c4]}) 7... Nc6 8.
O-O e5 9. d5 Ne7 10. e4 h6 11. Nd2 (11. Nh4 {Preventing ...f5.} g5 12. Qf3 (12.
Nf5 Nxf5 13. exf5 e4 $15 {[%csl Rf5]}) 12... Nfg8 13. Nf5 Nxf5 14. exf5 Kd7 $5
$15 {[%cal Yd7c7] Another typical motif in the position with a blocked center
and doubled c-pawns: after transferring the king to the perfectly safe square
c7, Black can advance his pawns on the kingside.}) 11... O-O 12. Re1 (12. f4
exf4 13. Rxf4 Ng6 14. Rf1 Ne5 $17 {[%csl Ge5]}) (12. Nb3 Nh7 13. f4 exf4 14.
Bxf4 Ng6 15. Bg3 f6 $15 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Yh7g5,Yd8e7,Yg6e5]}) 12... Nh7 13. Nf1
f5 $15 14. f3 $4 (14. f4 exf4 15. Bxf4 Ng6 $1 16. Qd2 (16. Bd2 f4 $19 {[%csl
Ge5][%cal Yg6e5,Yg7g5]}) 16... fxe4 17. Bxe4 Bf5 $17) ({We already know that
no matter what, White must take on f5.} 14. exf5 Bxf5 $15 {For example} 15.
Bxf5 Nxf5 16. Nd2 Qd7 17. Ne4 Nf6 $15) 14... f4 $1 $19 {Now it's pretty much
game over.} 15. a4 g5 16. h3 Ng6 17. Bd2 Nf6 {I bring my knights into the
attack since White does not have a plan.} 18. Re2 h5 19. Be1 g4 ({Today I
would have played} 19... Rf7 {with the idea of ...Rg7 and ...g4.}) 20. Rb2 g3 {
This idea, taken from the King's Indian, is far more effective than taking on
h3. Black is preparing a crushing sacrifice on h3.} 21. Nd2 Nh4 22. Bf1 Rf7 23.
a5 Rg7 24. Nb3 Nh7 25. Raa2 Ng5 26. Kh1 {White has organized his defence as
best as he could, but still Black crashes through.} Bxh3 27. gxh3 Qd7 28. Bg2
Nxg2 29. Rxg2 h4 {Black could have already taken on f3 before or now on h3.
With ...h4 he emphasizes that White is completely helpless.} 30. a6 b6 31. Nc1
Rf8 32. Nd3 Nxh3 33. Qa4 Qxa4 {Black can even exchange the queens since he is
going to collect the f3-pawn.} 34. Rxa4 Ng5 0-1

