{White to move Black is better in this position. He plans to play ...g5,
followed by doubling on the f-file. The question is: should White play a5 or
not?} 1. a5 $2 {The answer is that 1.a5 is a big mistake!} ({White had to
defend passively with something like} 1. Rf1 g5 $15 {[%cal Ya8f8]}) 1... bxa5
$1 2. Ra1 (2. Rb7 Nc8 3. Rxf7 (3. Rdb1 Nb6 $19) 3... Kxf7 $19 {[%csl Rc4,Gc8,
Re3][%cal Yc8b6]}) 2... Nc8 $1 {All of a sudden our knight gets a nice square
on b6, attacking the c4-pawn.} 3. Rxa5 Nb6 $17 {[%csl Gb6,Rc4][%cal Yb6c4]} *

