1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. g3 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 d6 6. Nf3 O-O 7. Bg2 Nc6 8.
Qd3 e5 9. Nd2 Re8 ({A better move is} 9... Rb8 $5 {with the idea of playing ...
Na5, ...b6, and ...Ba6.}) 10. O-O Qe7 {Now White played a horrible move after
which he is completely lost:} 11. e3 $4 ({After the correct} 11. e4 {White is
slightly better.}) 11... e4 $17 {Now we combine the light-square strategy with
play against the doubled c-pawns! Black has three minor pieces that can play
on the light squares. White has only two - the c1-bishop cannot control the
light squares. Putting the pawn on e4 is typical in connection with a
light-square strategy.} 12. Qc2 Bf5 13. Ba3 b6 14. Rab1 ({After} 14. c5 {
Black continues with} bxc5 ({After} 14... d5 15. Qb2 {the a3-f8 diagonal will
be opened though Black is still better.}) 15. dxc5 d5 {[%csl Ra3,Gc6,Ge5][%cal
Yc6e5,Ye7e6,Yf5h3,Ye6h3] We are not interested in taking on c5. Now the bishop
on a3 will stay out of the game.}) 14... Qd7 15. Rfd1 Rad8 16. Rb5 Na5 17. Rdb1
c6 18. R5b2 c5 {Black managed to completely block White's play. Here the
knight on a5 secures our queenside.} 19. Rb5 (19. d5 h5 {Our goal is to open
lines and attack on the kingside. The a3 bishop is totally out of play.} (19...
Bh3)) 19... Nc6 20. Bc1 Rc8 21. a4 h5 22. Nb3 Bh3 {Black is strategically
winning. The pawn on e4 secures a space advantage and the c1-bishop is
helpless in fighting against Black's play on the light squares.} 23. Bh1 h4 $19
{White later managed to miraculously save himself and make a draw.} 24. a5 Nxa5
25. Nxa5 bxa5 26. Rxa5 Rc7 27. Ba3 Qf5 28. Ra6 Rd8 29. Ra5 Bg4 30. Bg2 Rdc8 31.
Qd2 Bf3 32. Bf1 Qh5 33. Rbb5 Ng4 34. h3 hxg3 35. fxg3 Nf6 36. dxc5 dxc5 37. Qd6
Nd7 38. g4 Qh4 39. Rb1 Rc6 40. Qh2 Rh6 41. Rb2 Qe1 42. Qf2 Qxc3 43. Qd2 Qxd2
44. Rxd2 Rc7 45. Rd5 Rhc6 46. Kf2 a6 47. Kg3 f6 48. g5 fxg5 49. Rxg5 Rb7 50.
Bxc5 Nxc5 51. Raxc5 Rcb6 52. Rc8+ Kh7 53. c5 Rf6 54. h4 Rb1 55. Bh3 Rg1+ 56.
Kh2 Rh1+ 57. Kg3 g6 58. Re5 Rf7 59. Be6 Rg1+ 60. Kh3 Rf6 61. Bg8+ Kh6 62. Rc7
g5 63. hxg5+ Rxg5 64. Rxg5 Kxg5 65. Rg7+ Kf5 66. Rf7 Rxf7 67. Bxf7 Ke5 68. Kg3
a5 69. Bb3 Be2 70. Kf2 Bg4 71. Ke1 Be6 72. Bc2 Kd5 73. Bb3+ Ke5 74. Bc2 Bd7 75.
Kd2 Kd5 76. Kc3 Bc6 77. Bxe4+ Kxe4 78. Kb2 Kxe3 79. Ka3 Kd4 80. Kb2 a4 81. Ka1
a3 82. Ka2 Kxc5 83. Kxa3 1/2-1/2

