d6 9. a3 Bxc3 10. Bxc3 a4 $1 {Fixing the queenside is very useful for us, even
if we delay our development for one move.} 11. c5 {Weakening the light squares.
} ({White may try} 11. d5 {when we simply can play} Ne4 (11... exd5 12. Nh4 {
is not so clear.}) 12. Bb4 Nd7 $11) 11... Be4 12. Rc1 Nc6 13. cxb6 cxb6 14. Nd2
