11. Nxd4 Nc5 12. f3 d5 $40 (12... Nh5 $5)) 9... e5 (9... a5 {Here, fixing the
queenside is not a threat since White has strong play in the center. For
example} 10. Bd3 a4 11. O-O e5 12. e4 Re8 13. Rae1 exd4 14. Nxd4 Nc5 15. f4 $16
) 10. Be2 e4 {This is acceptable, though it would work better if White's
