1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Bd2 Nbd7 7. a3 Bxc3 8.
Bxc3 b6 (8... c5 $1) 9. e3 (9. e4 $1 $14) 9... Bb7 10. Be2 Ne4 11. O-O c5 (
11... f5 $5 12. Nd2 Qh4 13. Nxe4 fxe4 $1 $40 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Yf8f6,Yf6f5,
Yf5g5,Yf6g6,Yg6h6]}) (11... Nxc3 12. Qxc3 c5 13. Rfd1 Qe7 14. dxc5 dxc5 $11 {
Since White no longer has the pair of bishops, we can also take in this way.} (
14... Nxc5)) 12. Rfd1 cxd4 13. Bxd4 e5 14. Bc3 f5 15. b4 Rf6 16. Rab1 Qe7 $15
17. Ba1 $2 (17. Be1 Rg6 $15) 17... Rh6 {Black has a strong attack.} 18. c5 bxc5
19. bxc5 Ndxc5 20. Bc4+ Kh8 21. Bd5 Bxd5 22. Rxd5 Re6 {Black adjusts his plan:
he has an extra pawn, but without the light-squared bishop his attack is over.
That's why he must regroup his pieces and stabilize the position.} 23. h3 h6
24. Rdd1 Rf8 25. Qc4 f4 26. exf4 Rxf4 27. Rb8+ Kh7 28. Qc2 Rg6 29. Qa2 Ne6 30.
Rd3 Qc7 31. Qb1 Qc6 32. Qd1 Rf7 33. Nh4 Nxf2 34. Rxd6 Qc5 35. Qb1 Nd3+ 36. Kh2
Qxd6 0-1

