1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d6 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 Qe7 {Just a
logical move to get out of book.} 7. g3 Bd7 $5 8. Bg2 Bc6 9. f3 (9. Nf3 a5 10.
b3 Be4 $1 {We are familiar with this manoeuver.} 11. O-O Nbd7 12. Bb2 O-O 13.
Bh3 {White wants to move the knight from f3 without exchanging bishops.} b6 14.
Nd2 Bb7 15. f3 {Now we must attack the center - we cannot allow White to play
e4.} c5 16. e4 cxd4 17. Qxd4 {White has an advantage but he also has some
weaknesses which give us counterchances.} e5 $5) 9... d5 {White may be
theoretically slightly better, but Black has counter chances. In the end,
White pushed hard in an equal endgame and lost against the legendary Torre.}
10. b3 O-O 11. Nh3 Re8 12. O-O Nbd7 13. a4 e5 14. e3 Nf8 15. Nf2 Rad8 16. Nd3
Ng6 17. Nb4 Qe6 18. Nxc6 Qxc6 19. dxe5 Nxe5 20. Bb2 Qc5 21. Rad1 Nc6 22. Rfe1
