-100,-100,-239,-250,-453,-484,-476,-512,-516,-537,-550,-605,-974,-1103,-1167,
-1227,-1456,-1621,-1621,-1060]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3
c5 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. O-O Bxc3 8. bxc3 d6 9. Nd2 b6 10. Nb3 e5 11. f4 ({If White
allows it, with, let's say} 11. Rb1 $6 {, we push} e4 $1 12. Be2 {and
overprotect the pawn:} Re8 $17 {with a big strategical initiative. White's
bishops are kept at bay.}) 11... e4 12. Be2 Qd7 $1 $15 {A famous prophylactic
move - Black blocks the light squares by stopping g2-g4!} 13. h3 Ne7 14. Qe1 (
14. g4 h5 $15 {was problematic for White for concrete reasons. But maybe it
was still better than the game continuation.}) 14... h5 15. Bd2 Qf5 16. Kh2 Qh7
$1 $17 {Another famous maneuver. The queen works well from the seemingly
modest h7-square. The f5-square is vacated for the knight. Black's long-term
plan becomes ...g5, which he executes with success.} 17. a4 Nf5 18. g3 a5 19.
