1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Nf3 c5 6. Bd3 Nc6 7. O-O Bxc3 8.
bxc3 d6 9. e4 e5 10. d5 Ne7 11. Nh4 Ng6 12. Nf5 Nf4 13. Bc2 g6 14. Ne3 N4h5 {
One of the ideas to be aware of - Black moves the knight back to g7 and
prepares ...f5. But our recommended 14...Kh8 is better here.} ({Let's see
sample lines after} 14... Kh8 {, that show exactly why Black has excellent
prospects:} 15. f3 Rg8 (15... g5) 16. g3 Nh3+ 17. Kh1 h5 18. a4 Bd7 19. Qd2 Rg7
20. Qg2 Qe7 $17 {The engine won't tell you this, but such a position is, at
least in practice, clearly in Black's favour, as it's much easier for him to
generate clear-cut active play, e.g.} 21. Bd2 Rh7 22. a5 Rg8 $36 {We put all
the pieces on the kingside and start threatening to break through with ...g5
or ...h4.}) 15. g3 Ng7 16. f4 exf4 17. gxf4 Qe7 18. Qf3 Bd7 19. Re1 Rae8 20.
Ng2 Nfh5 21. Be3 Qd8 22. Bf2 Qc8 23. Bh4 Bg4 24. Qf2 Bh3 25. Ba4 Bd7 26. Bc2 f6
27. Bg3 Bh3 28. Re3 f5 29. e5 dxe5 30. Ba4 Bxg2 31. Bxe8 Nxe8 32. Kxg2 e4 33.
a4 Qc7 34. Kh1 Nd6 35. Qf1 Qa5 36. Bh4 Rf7 37. Bg5 Qa6 38. Rh3 Qxc4 39. Qg2 Ng7
40. Qd2 Nge8 41. a5 Rd7 42. Rd1 Nf7 43. Rg3 Nc7 44. Qg2 Rxd5 45. Rg1 Rd6 46.
Qh3 Nd5 47. Qh4 e3 48. Rh3 Qe4+ 49. Rg2 Nf6 0-1

