{[%evp 0,108,14,29,12,0,0,-4,29,29,32,32,20,23,23,20,36,41,34,22,22,25,25,30,
29,13,35,22,22,22,52,32,98,78,77,75,76,80,74,39,42,47,64,40,76,-40,-49,-56,-21,
-9,-52,-48,-54,-112,-118,-112,-15,-27,26,47,15,7,18,-60,-41,-73,-59,-53,-56,
-54,-89,-84,-84,-78,-74,-82,-80,-80,-80,-77,-73,-137,-132,-134,-119,-134,-134,
-136,-132,-132,-132,-132,-137,-127,-129,-127,-123,-120,-122,-122,-145,-137,
-182,-209,-207,-220,-206,-297,-267,-273,-272]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4.
e3 O-O 5. Bd3 c5 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. O-O Bxc3 8. bxc3 d6 9. e4 e5 10. d5 Ne7 11. Nh4
Ng6 12. Nf5 Nf4 13. Bc2 g6 14. Ne3 N4h5 {This move again. It makes sense and
can be a backup option, but 14...Kh8 remains our main move.} (14... Kh8) 15. f3
Ne8 16. g3 (16. Ng4 $1 $14 {was a more energetic idea for White that would
have left Black not fully satisfied with his position.}) 16... Neg7 17. Rf2 Bh3
18. Rb1 b6 19. Ng2 f5 {Black starts developing an initiative.} 20. Bh6 Qf6 21.
exf5 gxf5 22. Qd2 f4 23. Bxg7 Qxg7 24. g4 Nf6 $19 {After some suboptimal
choices by White, the resulting position is already terrible, in fact lost,
for him. ...h5 should come at some point, breaking through.} 25. Kh1 (25. Ne1
h5 $19) 25... Qg5 26. Rg1 Kh8 27. Qe1 Rae8 $6 ({Black should have broken
through with} 27... h5 $1 $19) 28. Re2 Nxg4 $2 {Unnecessary. White gets his
chances again.} (28... Rg8 $19 {followed by ...h5 remained completely
one-sided.}) 29. Nh4 Qf6 30. fxg4 f3 31. g5 $2 ({And here White could have
sacrificed an exchange to save himself from all the problems:} 31. Nf5 fxe2 32.
Qxe2 $11 {The point is that the bishop on h3 is shaky.}) 31... Qf4 32. g6 Rf6
33. g7+ Kg8 34. Rf2 Qxh4 35. Rxf3 Qxe1 36. Bxh7+ Kf7 37. Rxf6+ Kxf6 38. Rxe1
Kxg7 $17 {Black is back to clear domination, this time in the endgame, and
wins without trouble.} 39. Bd3 Kf6 40. Rg1 e4 41. Be2 Kf5 42. Rg3 Rh8 43. Kg1
Kf4 44. Kf2 Rh6 45. Kg1 a6 46. a3 Bd7 47. Kg2 Ba4 48. h3 Bd7 49. Bf1 b5 50.
cxb5 axb5 51. Kf2 c4 52. Bg2 Bf5 53. Re3 Rg6 54. Bf1 Rg8 0-1

