{[%evp 0,11,27,27,25,24,18,17,17,17,23,15,15,12] This section covers the model
games in the following line:} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 c5
6. Nge2 {I recommended this line in my course for White, as it's generally
promising. This time we will learn an adequate way for Black to react.} cxd4 7.
exd4 d5 8. cxd5 Qxd5 $1 {This recapture, rather than the more popular 8...Nxd5
move, shall be our choice. After} 9. O-O {We have three equally interesting
queen moves:} Qd7 $5 (9... Qh5 $5) ({and} 9... Qd8 $5) *

