{[%evp 0,84,24,24,24,14,25,25,26,30,24,18,16,20,20,29,30,24,50,50,48,33,25,27,
24,0,23,26,26,12,12,18,17,-53,-53,-47,-52,-59,-19,-18,-29,-41,-15,-29,87,89,80,
58,79,80,63,51,52,39,59,58,59,50,-9,-19,12,0,-8,-24,-24,-82,-10,-6,0,0,3,-11,
-5,-102,-96,-102,-113,-117,-102,-182,-184,-185,-195,-191,-197,-181,-187]} 1. d4
Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 c5 6. Nge2 d5 7. cxd5 cxd4 8. exd4
Qxd5 9. O-O Qh5 10. Ng3 $6 {By trading queens so easily, White immediately
goes on the defensive, since in the endgame he has no attacking chances and is
only left with an isolated pawn.} Qxd1 11. Rxd1 Nc6 12. Nge2 h6 13. Bf4 Rd8 14.
Bc7 Rd7 15. Bf4 b6 16. Rd2 Bb7 17. Rad1 Rad8 18. Be3 Kf8 19. a3 Be7 (19... Bxc3
$1 {was a good idea.} 20. bxc3 (20. Nxc3 {Giving up the pawn is the lesser
evil according to the engine!} Nxd4 21. Bb5 Nxb5 22. Rxd7 Rxd7 23. Rxd7 Nxd7
24. Nxb5 a6 25. Nd6 Bc6 $17 {Black is obviously for choice, but White may be
able to hold.}) 20... Na5 $17 {One kind of weakness has been transformed into
another one.}) 20. b4 Rc8 (20... Ng4 $1 $17 {was the best, with ...Nxe3, ...
Bg5 and ...e5 ideas.}) 21. Bb1 Nxb4 $2 {Black enters complications that are
not necessary and not favourable for him. He still wins at the end.} ({Black
should have kept grinding with} 21... Rcd8 $15) 22. axb4 Bxb4 23. Rc1 Rdc7 24.
Rdc2 Ba3 25. Nb5 Bxc1 26. Rxc7 Rxc7 27. Nxc7 Bxe3 28. fxe3 a6 29. Bd3 b5 30. e4
Ke7 31. h3 Kd7 32. e5 Ng8 33. Nxb5 axb5 34. Bxb5+ Bc6 35. Bxc6+ Kxc6 36. Nc3 $2
({It was necessary to improve the king's placement:} 36. Kf2 $1 $11 {Black
wouldn't be able to break through then.}) 36... Ne7 37. g4 Nd5 38. Ne4 Nf4 39.
h4 Kd5 40. Nd6 Kxd4 41. Nxf7 Ng6 42. h5 Nxe5 0-1

