{[%evp 0,15,19,31,25,-10,-11,-12,21,17,17,-4,-12,-3,17,18,14,18] In the second
part of the Black repertoire against the 4.e3 Nimzo, we take a look at two
major lines. One of them requires more concrete knowledge and the other more
conceptual knowledge. The theory of both lines is covered in detail in the
theory part included in part 1 of this repertoire.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3
Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. a3 (5. Nge2 d5 6. a3 Be7 {This is the line requiring more
general understanding.}) 5... Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 c5 7. Bd3 Nc6 8. Ne2 {This is the
line where some concrete memorization is best advised!} *

