{[%evp 0,16,19,34,19,-10,3,4,10,17,39,-3,-12,-4,11,18,19,17,26] This section
covers the games of the Saemisch Variation transposition, mainly reached via
the following move orders after 4.e3:} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 (4.
a3 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 {is the proper Saemisch, when the same position can be
reached, e.g.} c5 6. e3 O-O 7. Bd3 Nc6) 4... O-O 5. a3 (5. Bd3 c5 6. a3 Bxc3+
7. bxc3) 5... Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 c5 7. Bd3 Nc6 8. Ne2 b6 {The variation is not
dangerous for Black, but Black needs to know some specific lines and ideas
covered in the course, in order to be successful, as the game has a concrete
and double-edged character.} *

