10. Be3 Ba6 $1 11. Ng3 Na5 12. Qe2 Rc8 $36 (12... Nd6 $2 {This move wins a
pawn but runs into an attack that is not worth allowing:} 13. e5 Ndxc4 14. Qh5
g6 15. Qh6 $36) 13. d5 Qh4 $5 {This ...Qh4 move is quite common in such
positions!... so please keep it in mind!} 14. O-O Nd6 15. f4 f5 $1 {Generally,
it is always good to stop f4-f5 by White!} 16. Bf2 $2 (16. e5 Ndxc4 17. Rf3
$132 {This non-obvious move is required and that's exactly the problem with
White's position: BECAUSE HE HAS A VERY BAD PAWN STRUCTURE, HE MUST KEEP ON
PLAYING THE VERY BEST MOVES ALL THE TIME!... one mistake, one second rate move.
.. and he is much worse!}) 16... Qg4 {Black inevitably collects a pawn without
compensation for White.} 17. Qc2 Bxc4 18. e5 Ne4 19. Bxc4 Nxc4 20. Qd3 Ncd2 21.
Rfd1 {There are probably errors in the game notation around here.} Qxf4 22. Ne2
Qxe5 23. dxe6 dxe6 24. Rxd2 Nxd2 25. Qxd2 Rcd8 26. Qc2 f4 27. Re1 f3 28. Ng3
Qd5 29. gxf3 Rxf3 30. Ne4 Rd3 31. c4 Qf5 32. Qa4 Rd1 33. Qc6 Qg4+ 34. Kf1 h6
