{[%evp 0,18,20,20,17,17,17,25,26,26,23,13,13,13,13,13,13,13,14,14,14] This
part contains model games in the Rubinstein Variation, 5.Nge2} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4
e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Nge2 {My recommendation is the straightforward move}
d5 {with the following main lines:} 6. a3 Be7 7. cxd5 (7. Nf4 c6 8. Be2 Nbd7 9.
O-O dxc4 10. Bxc4 e5 $1 $132) 7... exd5 8. Nf4 (8. Ng3 c6 ({or} 8... c5) 9. Bd3
Re8 10. O-O Nbd7 $132) 8... c6 9. Bd3 Na6 $1 $132 {Intending ...Nc7-e6. The
variation doesn't contain forced variations and instead understanding of the
ideas described in the course is required for successful play.} *

