{Black played an amazing and almost flawless game!! Study it carefully!!} 1. d4
Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Nge2 d5 6. a3 Be7 7. cxd5 exd5 8. g3 $2 (
8. Nf4 c6 9. Bd3 Na6 10. O-O Nc7) 8... Nbd7 $3 9. Bg2 Nb6 $3 $15 10. O-O a5 11.
Nf4 Re8 12. a4 (12. f3 c5) 12... c6 13. b3 Bb4 $3 {preventing Ba3} ({Black
would be better even if she allowed the dark-squared bishops' exchange:} 13...
Bf5 $1 14. Ba3 Bxa3 15. Rxa3 Nc8 $1 {Directing the knight to the ideal
d6-square.} 16. Ra2 Nd6 $36 {White has not even played b4 yet, and Black will
soon start attacking on the kingside.}) 14. Qc2 Qe7 $1 {Stopping Ba3!} 15. Bb2
g6 $3 {Creating the f5-outpost for the bishop.} 16. Nd3 Bf5 17. Qe2 Bd6 $1 18.
Rfc1 $6 Nbd7 $1 {improving the worst placed piece!} 19. Nb1 h5 $1 20. Ba3 (20.
h4 $6 {is not a remedy. This move stops White for a moment, but White's
kingside shelter will be broken through by ...g5 and ...h4 sooner or later:}
Ng4 (20... Ne4) 21. Ba3 Bxa3 $1 22. Nxa3 g5 $3 23. hxg5 Bxd3 $1 (23... Qxg5 $17
) 24. Qxd3 Qxg5 $19 25. Re1 f5 (25... h4) (25... Ndf6)) 20... Bxa3 $1 21. Nxa3
h4 $1 22. Nc2 (22. Nb1 $5 Kg7 23. Nd2 Rh8 24. Re1 Rab8 {This line is shown for
instructive reasons, this specific move is obviously suboptimal, which is not
the point.} (24... Rae8 $1) 25. e4 dxe4 26. Nxe4 {This situation shows why
Black shouldn't release the tension on g3 prematurely. The centre is open, so
according to general rules, a flank attack becomes meaningless. That's why we
need to keep the option of ...h3, not ...hxg3, for such an occasion!} h3 $3 (
26... hxg3 $2 27. hxg3) 27. Bh1 Bxe4 (27... Rhe8 $17) 28. Bxe4 Qd6 $17) 22...
Kg7 $1 23. Nce1 hxg3 $1 {Black knows very well that now the center will not
open!... so it's time for a flank attack!!} 24. hxg3 Rh8 25. Nf3 Be4 26. Nc5
Nxc5 27. dxc5 Rh5 $1 {The final part of the decisive plan, doubling the rooks
on the h-file.} 28. Qb2 Qd7 29. Ne5 (29. Nd4 Bxg2 30. Kxg2 Qh3+ $19) 29... Qe6
30. f3 (30. Nf3 Rah8 {The end is very near.} 31. Nd4 (31. Ra2 Rh1+ 32. Bxh1
Rxh1+ 33. Kxh1 Qh3+ 34. Kg1 Bxf3 $19) 31... Rh1+ 32. Bxh1 Rxh1#) 30... Qxe5 31.
Qxe5 Rxe5 32. fxe4 Nxe4 33. Bxe4 Rxe4 34. Rc3 Rae8 35. Kf2 g5 36. Rd3 R8e6 37.
Rg1 f5 38. Rh1 Rh6 39. Rxh6 Kxh6 40. Rd1 Rb4 41. Rh1+ Kg6 42. Rh8 Rxb3 43. Rg8+
Kh5 44. Ke2 Kg4 45. Rg7 Rc3 46. Rxb7 Kxg3 47. Rf7 Kg4 48. Ra7 Rxc5 49. Ra8 f4
50. exf4 Kxf4 51. Rf8+ Kg3 52. Rf3+ Kg4 53. Rf6 Rc4 54. Ke3 c5 55. Rc6 Kf5 0-1

