{[%evp 0,86,16,13,30,-10,-10,-1,4,20,26,-4,1,12,8,9,21,25,21,18,17,13,20,3,7,
-37,-9,-20,-10,-6,-9,-40,-42,-19,-41,-37,-41,-38,-1,-26,-36,-85,-38,-84,-108,
-122,-106,-87,-55,-131,-229,-127,-118,-218,-208,-194,-136,-117,-167,-167,-88,
-89,-95,-83,-102,-178,-195,-233,-254,-483,-482,-483,-325,-466,-417,-409,-281,
-286,-272,-255,-245,-383,-254,-281,-314,-296,-307,-325,-325]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4
e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Nge2 d5 6. a3 Be7 7. cxd5 exd5 8. Nf4 c6 9. Bd3 Bd6
$5 {This also looks playable... but i think 9...Na6! is simpler!} 10. O-O Re8
11. Qc2 {By playing this Qc2, White deprives himself of the f3-e4 plan,
because d4 pawn will always be hanging!} (11. f3 $1 b6 $3 {This is the way to
go against the f3-e4 plan!} 12. Kh1 (12. e4 $2 dxe4 13. Nxe4 (13. fxe4 $2 Bxf4
14. Bxf4 Qxd4+ 15. Kh1 Bg4 $3 16. Qd2 $1 (16. Qc2 Nbd7 $17) 16... Rd8 $3 $17 (
16... Nbd7 $4 17. e5 Nxe5 18. Bxh7+) 17. e5 Qxd3 18. Qxd3 Rxd3 19. exf6 Nd7 20.
fxg7 Kxg7 $17) 13... Ba6 $15) (12. g4 Ba6 $1 13. Rf2 Bxd3 14. Nxd3 h6 15. Rg2
c5 $15 16. h4 Nc6 17. g5 cxd4 18. exd4 hxg5 19. Bxg5 Nxd4 $17) 12... Ba6 13.
Bxa6 Nxa6 $132 {Take account of a major positional idea:} 14. Qc2 $2 (14. e4
Bxf4 15. Bxf4 dxe4 16. Qa4 Nc7 $15) 14... Bxf4 15. exf4 c5 $17 16. dxc5 bxc5 $1
{Creating strong hanging pawns.} 17. f5 h6 $17) 11... Nbd7 $1 12. b4 $6 Nf8 $15
13. h3 Ne6 $5 (13... Ng6 $1 $15) 14. Nxe6 (14. Nfe2 $2 Ng5 $36 {White runs
into kingside problems.} 15. Bf5 Nge4 16. Bxc8 Rxc8 17. Nxe4 dxe4 $17 (17...
Nxe4 $17) (17... Rxe4 $17)) 14... Bxe6 $15 15. b5 cxb5 $3 {It turns out the
whole minority attack is not anything special in a situation with so active
pieces for Black, especially the dark-squared bishop.} 16. Bxb5 (16. Nxb5 Rc8
$3 {Remember, in such situation we always want to move the rook out of the
corner and tuck the bishop back on b8!} 17. Qb2 (17. Qa4 $2 {fails tactically!}
Qd7 18. Qxa7 Ra8 (18... Bxh3 $19 19. Nxd6 Qg4 20. g3 Qf3 21. Kh2 Qg2#) 19. Qb6
Ra6 $19) 17... Bb8 $17 {Black has a huge advantage. Dark clouds will gather
over White's kingside.}) 16... Re7 17. Bd2 Rc8 18. Rfc1 Bb8 19. Bf1 Ne4 20. g3
Rec7 21. Qb2 Ng5 $1 $17 {Of course, Black goes for an attack!} 22. f4 (22. h4
Nf3+ 23. Kg2 Nxh4+ 24. gxh4 Qxh4 $19) 22... Nxh3+ $1 23. Kg2 (23. Kh2 Nf2 $19)
